<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-337] flock example should mount using mgs not mds</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-337</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The mount command example in section 36.19.4.1 should mount using mgs@tcp instead of mds@tcp&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;36.19.4.1. Example&lt;br/&gt;
$ mount -t lustre -o flock mds@tcp0:/lustre /mnt/client&lt;br/&gt;
You can check it in /etc/mtab. It should look like,&lt;br/&gt;
mds@tcp0:/lustre /mnt/client lustre rw,flock 0 0&lt;/p&gt;</description>
